name: Abnormalities, Severe Teratoid
description: Marked developmental anomalies of a fetus or infant.
label: Disease

name: Abruptio Placentae
description: Premature separation of the normally implanted PLACENTA from the UTERUS. Signs of varying degree of severity include UTERINE BLEEDING, uterine MUSCLE HYPERTONIA, and FETAL DISTRESS or FETAL DEATH.
label: Disease

name: Acantholysis
description: Separation of the prickle cells of the stratum spinosum of the epidermis, resulting in atrophy of the prickle cell layer. It is seen in diseases such as pemphigus vulgaris (see PEMPHIGUS) and DARIER DISEASE.
label: Disease

name: Acatalasia
description: A rare autosomal recessive disorder resulting from the absence of CATALASE activity. Though usually asymptomatic, a syndrome of oral ulcerations and gangrene may be present.
label: Disease

name: hypogonadotropic hypogonadism 24 without anosmia
description: Any hypogonadotropic hypogonadism in which the cause of the disease is a mutation in the FSHB gene.
label: Disease
